  <title>murmur — open‑source reliability harness for coding agents</title>
  <meta name="description" content="murmur is an open‑source reliability harness that gives you continuous evaluation, drift detection and open observability for coding agents." />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css" />
</head>
<body>
  <header class="site-header">
    <div class="container">
      <a href="/" class="logo" aria-label="murmur home">murmur</a>
      <nav class="site-nav" aria-label="Main navigation">
        <a href="#features">Features</a>
        <a href="#metrics">Metrics</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/murmur" rel="external">GitHub</a>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main>
    <!-- HERO -->
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="container">
        <h1 class="hero-headline">murmur</h1>
        <p class="hero-subhead">The open‑source reliability harness for coding agents.</p>
        <p class="hero-description">
          Ship AI‑assisted code with confidence. Evaluate every commit, detect drift the moment it appears, and keep your agents accountable — without surrendering visibility to a black box.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-actions">
          <a href="https://github.com/murmur" class="btn btn-primary" rel="external">View on GitHub</a>
          <a href="#metrics" class="btn btn-secondary">See the numbers</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- METRICS STRIP -->
    <section id="metrics" class="metrics-strip" aria-labelledby="metrics-heading">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 id="metrics-heading" class="metrics-heading">Live Reliability Benchmarks</h2>
        <div class="metrics-grid">
          <div class="metric">
            <span class="metric-label">pass@1</span>
            <span class="metric-value">94.7%</span>
            <span class="metric-note">single‑sample accuracy</span>
          </div>
          <div class="metric">
            <span class="metric-label">pass^k</span>
            <span class="metric-value">99.3%</span>
            <span class="metric-note">k=10 consensus pass</span>
          </div>
          <div class="metric">
            <span class="metric-label">variance</span>
            <span class="metric-value">&plusmn;1.2%</span>
            <span class="metric-note">week‑over‑week drift</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FEATURES -->
    <section id="features" class="features" aria-labelledby="features-heading">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 id="features-heading" class="section-heading">What murmur does</h2>
        <div class="features-grid">
          <article class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">&#9656;</div>
            <h3 class="feature-title">Continuous Evaluation</h3>
            <p class="feature-body">
              Every pull request triggers a full reliability sweep. Murmur runs your agent against a curated benchmark and surfaces pass@1, pass@k, and latency metrics before code reaches production — so you know exactly whether the latest prompt tweak helped or hurt.
            </p>
          </article>
          <article class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">&#9679;</div>
            <h3 class="feature-title">Drift Detection</h3>
            <p class="feature-body">
              Prompts evolve and models shift beneath you — often silently. Murmur tracks variance across versions and alerts your team the moment reliability strays outside your thresholds. Catch the dip before your customers do.
            </p>
          </article>
          <article class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">&#9632;</div>
            <h3 class="feature-title">Open Observability</h3>
            <p class="feature-body">
              No proprietary dashboards, no vendor lock‑in. Murmur exports every run as structured JSON logs and plugs into your existing stack — Prometheus, Grafana, or plain CSV. Your data stays yours, always.
            </p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- TESTIMONIAL -->
    <section class="testimonial" aria-labelledby="testimonial-heading">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 id="testimonial-heading" class="section-heading">Trusted by teams shipping agent‑generated code</h2>
        <blockquote class="testimonial-quote">
          <p>
            Before Murmur, we were flying blind. Our coding agent’s pass@1 dropped from 91% to 76% over a month and we didn’t notice until a customer filed a bug. Now we catch drift within hours. It’s not optional — it’s infrastructure.
          </p>
          <footer class="testimonial-attribution">
            <cite class="testimonial-author">Sarah Chen</cite>
            <span class="testimonial-role">Engineering Lead, Cascade Labs</span>
          </footer>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

